We isolate $x$ by dividing both sides by 3 (a positive number):
$$
 3x &> 12 \\
 \frac{3x}{3} &> \frac{12}{3} \\
 x &> 4
$$

The solution is all real numbers greater than 4.

- Graph: tikzpicture[scale=0.5, baseline=-0.5ex]
 (1,0) – (9,0);
 in {2,3,4,5,6,7,8} {
 (, 0.1) – (, -0.1) node[below] { $\x$};
 }
 (4,0) – (8.8,0);
 (4,0) circle (3pt);
 tikzpicture

- Interval notation: $(4, \infty)$

**Check:** Let $x = 6$: $3(6) > 12 \implies 18 > 12$

We isolate $x$ by dividing both sides by $-4$. Since $-4$ is negative, we 
**reverse the inequality symbol**:
align*
 -4x & 20 \\[4pt]
 \frac{-4x}{-4} &\leq \frac{20}{-4} \qquad\text{(flip the symbol!)} \\[4pt]
 x &\leq -5
\end{align*}

The solution is all real numbers less than or equal to $-5$.
\begin{itemize}
 \item Graph: \begin{tikzpicture}[scale=0.5, baseline=-0.5ex]
 \draw[thick, ->] (-9,0) -- (-1,0);
 \foreach \x in {-8,-7,-6,-5,-4,-3,-2} {
 \draw (\x, 0.1) -- (\x, -0.1) node[below] {\scriptsize $\x$};
 }
 \draw[AtlasTeal, very thick, ->] (-5,0) -- (-8.8,0);
 ll[AtlasTeal] (-5,0) circle (3pt);
 \end{tikzpicture}
 \item Interval notation: $(-\infty, -5]$
\end{itemize}

\textbf{Check:} Let $x = -6$ (in the solution set):
\[
 -4(-6) \geq 20 \implies 24 \geq 20 \quad\checkmark
\]
Let $x = -4$ (not in the solution set):
\[
 -4(-4) \geq 20 \implies 16 \geq 20 \quad\text{False } \checkmark
\]
